      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Minimum wage increases inevitably raise operational costs for small businesses, which is a direct burden on their bottom line. In low cost-of-living areas, these businesses are often already operating on razor-thin margins, making wage hikes a significant financial strain. To maintain profitability, these businesses frequently have to either raise prices for consumers or cut back on hiring and services. Therefore, these mandates often force small businesses to become more conservative in their growth strategies.",
