      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument that higher wages stimulate the local economy is a well-established economic principle, often called the multiplier effect. When low-wage workers earn more, they spend that extra income immediately on local goods and services, directly boosting demand for small businesses. This increased consumer spending creates a virtuous cycle, leading to higher revenue and potentially more stable employment for everyone.",
      "source": "target",
